To Install wireguard client on Ubuntu:
A.. To install wireguard, run below commands:


sudo add-apt-repository ppa:wireguard/wireguard
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install wireguard-dkms wireguard-tools
sudo apt-get install openresolv


B. create a new peer in korplink portal (Name the peer accordingly For
Ex HR application server)


C.  create a configuration file like below and paste the contents from
peer configuration file created from Korplink portal. To save , ctrl s
and ctrl x


sudo nano /etc/wireguard/wg0.conf


D. Start wireguard and make wireguard start automatically on server boot


sudo systemctl start wg-quick@wg0
sudo systemctl enable wg-quick@wg0
